<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1187">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Grip</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Sweden and Norway</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge receipt of your excellency’s note of the 15th instant by
                            which you are pleased to inform me of the forms which the Government of
                            the United States desires to see observed by the neutral vessels of war
                            which are destined for blockaded ports in the island of Cuba and
                            particularly for Habana.</p>
                        <p>I shall not fail to advise my Government without delay of this important
                            communication.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Grip.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>